1.title: King of the Gulf
1.plot: When Buddy discovers that a fishing boat has missed its delivery, he recruits his brother Kenny and his son Hans to hit the water in a mad dash to catch and deliver 15,000 pounds of red snapper in 36 hours.

2.title: Blackjack Is Back
2.plot: At Katie's Seafood House a batch of bad Snapper has Buddy at Nicks throat, and Hans back on the open sea to pull in an emergency haul.

3.title: Warsaw Pact
3.plot: At Katie's Seafood House Buddy tries to impress a top customer at the cost of Kenny's crews pay. At sea, Hans looks to gain notoriety in catching the fabled Warsaw grouper.

4.title: Hit Rock Bottom
4.plot: At Katie's Seafood House the quota has increased and so have the problems, Nick and Hans are both forced to make tough decisions that could ultimately prove costly to Katie's bottom line.

5.title: Clash of the Guindon's
5.plot: Hans and Kenny go head to head in a fishing competition to fill Nicks 10K pound snapper order, Buddy looks for illegal fisherman, and Ricky struggles with Katie's online business.

6.title: All Fish and No Play
6.plot: At the end of a long fishing trip, Hans struggles to catch snapper, while Buddy heads to Austin to lobby on behalf of his fellow fishermen.

7.title: Hurricane Buddy
7.plot: Kenny and Nick deal with the aftermath of Hurricane Buddy at Katie's Seafood; Hans is up against a grouper fisherman's smartest adversaries; and Ricky hopes to fill his dad's shoes in the political arena.

8.title: Deckhand Down
8.plot: At prosperous time at Katie's seafood is disrupted when Buddy has to make an emergency Run to The BlackJack to help one of Hans's deckhands who's in dire need.

imdb.plot outline: Big Fish Texas follows Galveston's Guindon family as they try to keep Katie's Seafood Market - their family business - growing and thriving at all costs. A homegrown enterprise built both on land and at sea, the challenges at Katie's are everywhere. On the water, they battle against long days, longer nights, a sea full of predators, and Mother Nature's whims. At home base, they struggle to juggle surpluses, shortages, and orders while also processing a quarter of the Gulf's deep-water fish and spearheading initiatives to preserve their fishery. But no matter how busy the business keeps them, at the end of the day this is a family built on old-fashioned values, and they'd never miss an opportunity to get together for a good laugh and a home-cooked meal.
